title: Meet the Allies
body:
Henry Calvin Wilson

Information:

Parents: Samuel Wilson

Other Family: 

  • Fredrick John Wilson- Younger Brother

DOB: March 30, 1989

SO: Homosexual

Current Status: Lawyer for the Avengers

Favorite Team Member: Doesn't’ like to pick favorites

Random Facts:

Henry attended the SHIELD Academy of Operations after his basic education at the SHIELD Academy of Primary and Secondary Education. When he was about to graduate he realized that he didn’t want to go into the secret agent life. So on the night before graduation, he quit and left.

title: Venom in the MCU
body:
Eddie Brock, Bruce Banner, and Bucky Barnes relate over having a dangerous alter-ego sharing their body. 

Venom, the Hulk, and the Winter Soldier relate over having to rent a body from a peaceful pansy 

Captain America is giving one of his usual “inspiring” speeches of heroic gibberish, that Eddie is attempting to politely listen (or pretend to listen) to. Venom keeps heckling the Cap quietly in Eddie’s head, picking apart all of the problems with his heroic word salad, with Eddie begging his symbiot to shut up.

Wanda Maximoff, a telepath, would be the only one hearing Eddie and Venom’s mental conversation, and keep tossing them awkward looks.

Since Tony Stark has to have snark-banter with everyone capable, he gets into a disagreement with “Eddie,” not realizing it’s really Venom he’s talking to. His annoyance is coupled by nervous prying about what the heck keeps happening to Eddie’s voice. 

  • Tony: “Seriously, it’s like you keep bouncing in and out of puberty, are they bungee jumping down there?” 
  • Eddie: “Okay um, how do I put this–”
  • Venom: “Stark is looking delicious.”
  • Tony: “Wow, you don’t keep up with tabloids do you. I’m engaged now, you’re a decade late for Tony Stark the Playboy.”
  • Eddie: (Hissing) “That’s enough, Venom!”
  • Tony: “Who…..? Don’t tell me you have a Hulk Winter Gollum Thing too…”
  • Eddie: “Gotta go, catch you later.” (Dashes off)
  • Tony: (Mutters) “And they say I belong in a straight jacket.” 

Peter Parker, poor BB, ends up in the wrong place at the wrong time. Venom temporarily leaves Eddie and possesses Peter, and makes him do an embarrassing Emo dance, in front of several people–including Mr. Stark, M.J., and Flash Thompson. 

Thaddeus Ross has his important political lobster dinner ruined by Eddie and Venom, with bonus quips from Tony, and a satisfied look of long overdue revenge from Bruce. 

But Nick Fury would be to Venom what the Bloody Baron is to Peeves
